<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="reporter">Reporter</a> - In the context of <a href="#geneExpression">gene expression</a>, a reporter allows the easy determination of <a href="#transcription">transcription</a> from a given <a href="#promoter">promoter</a>. Good reporters have an obvious <a href="#phenotype">phenotype</a> such as the blue <a href="#phenotype">phenotype</a> for <a href="#lacz">LacZ</a> in the presence of <a href="#x_gal">X-gal</a>, or the <a href="#fluorescence">fluorescence</a> of a <a href="#green_fluorescent_protein_gfp_egfp">fluorescent protein</a>. <a href="#quantitative">Quantification</a> of <a href="#protein">protein</a> production from a <a href="#promoter">promoter</a> as a function of reporter <a href="#fluorescence">fluorescence</a> is also possible.